& =\frac{q}{(l-L)^{2}-R^{2}} \sqrt{\frac{R l}{4 \pi \varepsilon_{0}} \frac{1}{m L}}
\end{aligned}
\tag{20}
$$

The energy of mutual interactions of induced charges on the surface of the sphere is given with

$$
\begin{aligned}
& E_{e l, 2}=\frac{1}{2} \frac{1}{4 \pi \varepsilon_{0}} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \sum_{\substack{j=1 \\
j \neq i}}^{N} \frac{q_{i} q_{j}}{\left|\vec{r}_{i}-\vec{r}_{j}\right|} \\
& =\frac{1}{2} \frac{1}{4 \pi \varepsilon_{0}} \sum_{i=1}^{N} q_{i} \frac{q^{\prime}}{\left|\vec{r}_{i}-\vec{d}^{\prime}\right|}= \\
& =-\frac{1}{2} \frac{1}{4 \pi \varepsilon_{0}} \sum_{i=1}^{N} q_{i} \frac{q}{\left|\vec{r}_{i}-\vec{d}\right|}= \\
