\end{aligned}
$$
$$
\begin{aligned}

E_{\text {ind }}(r) & =-\frac{r}{2} \frac{d B}{d t} \tag{A-2}

\end{aligned}

$$



This induced field exerts a torque on the cylinder, causing it to rotate:



$$

\begin{aligned}

\tau & =2 \pi a \cdot \frac{\lambda}{2 \pi a} \cdot E_{\text {ind }}(a) \cdot a=I \cdot \frac{d \omega}{d t}
\end{aligned} \tag{A1-3}
